		<title>GBPUSD Awaits British GDP Growth Data</title>
		<link>https://www.atfx.com/en/analysis/market-news/gbpusd-awaits-british-gdp-growth-data</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[ATFX]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Fri, 14 Mar 2025 01:06:45 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Market news & Insights]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[GBPUSD]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Recent news]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.atfx.com/?p=46869</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[The GBPUSD exchange rate is awaiting GDP growth data from the British economy on Friday. GBPUSD &#8211; Daily Chart GBPUSD has a key target to the upside at 1.34 but needs to get above the 1.30 level first. The GDP release could give a catalyst for that, or could lead to a correction after a [&#8230;]]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The </span><a href="https://www.atfx.com.bz/en/live-chart/gbp-usd" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">GBPUSD</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> exchange rate is awaiting GDP growth data from the British economy on Friday.</span></p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-46871" src="https://www.atfx.com.bz/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/GBPUSD-Daily-Chart.png" alt="GBPUSD - Daily Chart" width="770" height="576" srcset="https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/GBPUSD-Daily-Chart.png 770w, https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/GBPUSD-Daily-Chart-300x224.png 300w, https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/GBPUSD-Daily-Chart-768x575.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 770px) 100vw, 770px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-weight: 400; font-size: 10pt;">GBPUSD &#8211; Daily Chart</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">GBPUSD has a key target to the upside at 1.34 but needs to get above the 1.30 level first. The GDP release could give a catalyst for that, or could lead to a correction after a sharp rally in 2025.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The GDP data is released at 3pm HKT and is expected to show a monthly gain of 0.1%, down from 0.4% previously.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">A leading UK business group has predicted a “long and challenging year” for the country. The British Chambers of Commerce said higher taxes and a looming global trade war were the causes. It now expects GDP to be just 0.9% higher by the end of 2025, a sharp downgrade from a previous forecast of 1.3%.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The limited growth expected this year will also be driven by higher Government spending rather than a busy private sector, the BCC warned. The BCC added that employers will struggle to invest in 2025, as they struggle to cope with rises in National Insurance tax and the minimum wage.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Another round of tariffs by Donald Trump on products such as steel is another concern for the UK.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">John Foster, policy officer at the CBI business group, said: “At a moment in the economic cycle when boosting business confidence and unlocking firms’ capacity for investment holds the key to kick-starting economic growth, the escalating tariff situation in the US remains deeply concerning.” </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The coming GDP numbers will be important to see if the UK can shake off the recent gloom and a sharp unwind in the US dollar against global </span><a href="https://www.atfx.com.bz/en/markets/forex-trading" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span style="font-weight: 400;">currencies</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> may also be reassessed.</span></p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
